This has been bugging for a long time

!2952156845-build_status.png|thumbnail!

You can see the difference when you give icon {{width: 17px}}

Consider these 2 examples:

{code}
#!markdown

List:
 - first
{code}

{code}
#!markdown

List:

 - first
{code}

First one is interpreted incorrectly(list syntax isn&#x27;t recognized, leading to list collapsing into one string), while second one is recongnized.

Issue occurs only on repo base pages, with README.MD file being in repo root.

With two legged auth disabled on my account the following (replace with your own credentials) was working perfectly fine up until a few days ago :-

{code}
#!bash
curl -X POST -u "client_id:secret" \
      https://bitbucket.org/site/oauth2/access_token -d grant_type=password \
      -d username={username} -d password={password}
{code}

Something has changed and now it has stopped working and it always responds with

{"error_description": "Invalid resource owner username/password", "error": "invalid_request"}

We do not support using OAuth to access the SSH endpoints on the Bitbucket API at this point in time.\\
However, when trying to perform a call to this endpoint, like the example below:

{code}
#!bash
curl -X POST https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/users/<user>/ssh-keys -H &#x27;Accept:application/json&#x27; -H &#x27;Authorization: Bearer <token>&#x27; -H &#x27;Content-Type: application/json&#x27; 
-d &#x27;{ "label": "<label>", "key":"<ssh_key>" }&#x27;

{code}

The API returns this response:

{code}
#!bash
{"type": "error","error":{ "message": "Something went wrong", "id": "<code>" }}

{code}

It should actually return a 403 error.

White page when viewing file history. This error appears in my browser console:

{code}
#!javascript

TypeError: "t.parents is undefined"
{code}
